cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper focuses on visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method utilizes an LSTM network, which is a type of recurrent neural network commonly used in natural language processing and time series analysis (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of data augmentation based on GANs, which is a popular technique in deep learning for generating synthetic data to improve model performance (cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on visual tracking benchmarks, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) subcategories.
